{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1039,"text":"I'd like to invite you to close your eyes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":6063,"text":"Imagine yourself standing\noutside the front door of your home."},{"time":11979,"text":"I'd like you to notice\nthe color of the door,"},{"time":14792,"text":"the material that it's made out of."},{"time":19241,"text":"Now visualize a pack\nof overweight nudists on bicycles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25060,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":26515,"text":"They are competing\nin a naked bicycle race,"},{"time":29213,"text":"and they are headed straight\nfor your front door."},{"time":32458,"text":"I need you to actually see this."},{"time":34323,"text":"They are pedaling\nreally hard, they're sweaty,"},{"time":38084,"text":"they're bouncing around a lot."},{"time":41259,"text":"And they crash straight\ninto the front door of your home."},{"time":45518,"text":"Bicycles fly everywhere,\nwheels roll past you,"},{"time":48771,"text":"spokes end up in awkward places."},{"time":52566,"text":"Step over the threshold of your door\ninto your foyer, your hallway,"},{"time":56899,"text":"whatever's on the other side,"},{"time":58502,"text":"and appreciate the quality of the light."},{"time":62254,"text":"The light is shining\ndown on Cookie Monster."},{"time":68837,"text":"Cookie Monster is waving at you\nfrom his perch on top of a tan horse."},{"time":73496,"text":"It's a talking horse."},{"time":75304,"text":"You can practically feel\nhis blue fur tickling your nose."},{"time":80144,"text":"You can smell the oatmeal raisin cookie\nthat he's about to shovel into his mouth."},{"time":84114,"text":"Walk past him."},{"time":85740,"text":"Walk past him into your living room."},{"time":88238,"text":"In your living room,\nin full imaginative broadband,"},{"time":91341,"text":"picture Britney Spears."},{"time":94373,"text":"She is scantily clad, she's dancing\non your coffee table,"},{"time":99496,"text":"and she's singing\n\"Hit Me Baby One More Time.\""},{"time":102361,"text":"And then, follow me into your kitchen."},{"time":105091,"text":"In your kitchen, the floor has been\npaved over with a yellow brick road,"},{"time":109385,"text":"and out of your oven are coming\ntowards you Dorothy, the Tin Man,"},{"time":114792,"text":"the Scarecrow and the Lion\nfrom \"The Wizard of Oz,\""},{"time":117737,"text":"hand-in-hand, skipping\nstraight towards you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120000,"text":"Okay. Open your eyes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125086,"text":"I want to tell you\nabout a very bizarre contest"},{"time":128213,"text":"that is held every spring\nin New York City."},{"time":131475,"text":"It's called the United States\nMemory Championship."},{"time":134522,"text":"And I had gone to cover\nthis contest a few years back"},{"time":137260,"text":"as a science journalist,"},{"time":139149,"text":"expecting, I guess, that this was going\nto be like the Superbowl of savants."},{"time":145388,"text":"This was a bunch of guys and a few ladies,"},{"time":148656,"text":"widely varying in both age\nand hygienic upkeep."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152869,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":155999,"text":"They were memorizing\nhundreds of random numbers,"},{"time":159359,"text":"looking at them just once."},{"time":160771,"text":"They were memorizing the names of dozens\nand dozens and dozens of strangers."},{"time":165969,"text":"They were memorizing\nentire poems in just a few minutes."},{"time":169151,"text":"They were competing\nto see who could memorize"},{"time":171404,"text":"the order of a shuffled pack\nof playing cards the fastest."},{"time":174889,"text":"I was like, this is unbelievable."},{"time":176873,"text":"These people must be freaks of nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180404,"text":"And I started talking\nto a few of the competitors."},{"time":183318,"text":"This is a guy called Ed Cook,\nwho had come over from England,"},{"time":186682,"text":"where he had one\nof the best-trained memories."},{"time":188920,"text":"And I said to him,\n\"Ed, when did you realize"},{"time":192524,"text":"that you were a savant?\""},{"time":194810,"text":"And Ed was like, \"I'm not a savant."},{"time":197320,"text":"In fact, I have just an average memory."},{"time":199652,"text":"Everybody who competes\nin this contest will tell you"},{"time":202685,"text":"that they have just an average memory."},{"time":204829,"text":"We've all trained ourselves to perform\nthese utterly miraculous feats of memory"},{"time":211722,"text":"using a set of ancient techniques,"},{"time":213713,"text":"techniques invented\n2,500 years ago in Greece,"},{"time":216535,"text":"the same techniques that Cicero\nhad used to memorize his speeches,"},{"time":221527,"text":"that medieval scholars had used\nto memorize entire books.\""},{"time":226070,"text":"And I said, \"Whoa. How come\nI never heard of this before?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":230205,"text":"And we were standing\noutside the competition hall,"},{"time":232665,"text":"and Ed, who is a wonderful, brilliant,\nbut somewhat eccentric English guy,"},{"time":239055,"text":"says to me, \"Josh, you're\nan American journalist."},{"time":243546,"text":"Do you know Britney Spears?\""},{"time":246023,"text":"I'm like, \"What? No. Why?\""},{"time":250763,"text":"\"Because I really want\nto teach Britney Spears"},{"time":253217,"text":"how to memorize the order\nof a shuffled pack of playing cards"},{"time":256121,"text":"on U.S. national television."},{"time":257931,"text":"It will prove to the world\nthat anybody can do this.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":261034,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":266263,"text":"I was like, \"Well, I'm not Britney Spears,"},{"time":269740,"text":"but maybe you could teach me."},{"time":272455,"text":"I mean, you've got to start\nsomewhere, right?\""},{"time":274740,"text":"And that was the beginning\nof a very strange journey for me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278745,"text":"I ended up spending\nthe better part of the next year"},{"time":281713,"text":"not only training my memory,"},{"time":283531,"text":"but also investigating it,"},{"time":285491,"text":"trying to understand how it works,"},{"time":287499,"text":"why it sometimes doesn't work,"},{"time":289502,"text":"and what its potential might be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292176,"text":"And I met a host\nof really interesting people."},{"time":294393,"text":"This is a guy called E.P."},{"time":296287,"text":"He's an amnesic who had, very possibly,"},{"time":298583,"text":"the worst memory in the world."},{"time":301292,"text":"His memory was so bad,"},{"time":303085,"text":"that he didn't even remember\nhe had a memory problem,"},{"time":306030,"text":"which is amazing."},{"time":307588,"text":"And he was this incredibly tragic figure,"},{"time":309566,"text":"but he was a window into the extent\nto which our memories make us who we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316046,"text":"At the other end\nof the spectrum, I met this guy."},{"time":318697,"text":"This is Kim Peek, he was the basis\nfor Dustin Hoffman's character"},{"time":322348,"text":"in the movie \"Rain Man.\""},{"time":324022,"text":"We spent an afternoon together\nin the Salt Lake City Public Library"},{"time":328212,"text":"memorizing phone books,"},{"time":330367,"text":"which was scintillating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332970,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":335727,"text":"And I went back and I read\na whole host of memory treatises,"},{"time":339909,"text":"treatises written 2,000-plus\nyears ago in Latin,"},{"time":344321,"text":"in antiquity, and then later,\nin the Middle Ages."},{"time":347456,"text":"And I learned a whole bunch\nof really interesting stuff."},{"time":350670,"text":"One of the really interesting\nthings that I learned"},{"time":353240,"text":"is that once upon a time,"},{"time":355514,"text":"this idea of having a trained,\ndisciplined, cultivated memory"},{"time":361806,"text":"was not nearly so alien\nas it would seem to us to be today."},{"time":366782,"text":"Once upon a time,\npeople invested in their memories,"},{"time":371071,"text":"in laboriously furnishing their minds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376716,"text":"Over the last few millenia,"},{"time":378219,"text":"we've invented a series of technologies --"},{"time":380965,"text":"from the alphabet, to the scroll,"},{"time":383375,"text":"to the codex, the printing\npress, photography,"},{"time":385694,"text":"the computer, the smartphone --"},{"time":387985,"text":"that have made it progressively\neasier and easier"},{"time":390540,"text":"for us to externalize our memories,"},{"time":393370,"text":"for us to essentially outsource\nthis fundamental human capacity."},{"time":399737,"text":"These technologies have made\nour modern world possible,"},{"time":403016,"text":"but they've also changed us."},{"time":405047,"text":"They've changed us culturally,"},{"time":406758,"text":"and I would argue that they've\nchanged us cognitively."},{"time":409916,"text":"Having little need to remember anymore,"},{"time":412646,"text":"it sometimes seems\nlike we've forgotten how."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415734,"text":"One of the last places on Earth\nwhere you still find"},{"time":418313,"text":"people passionate about this idea of\na trained, disciplined, cultivated memory,"},{"time":423730,"text":"is at this totally singular\nmemory contest."},{"time":426377,"text":"It's actually not that singular,"},{"time":428045,"text":"there are contests held\nall over the world."},{"time":430090,"text":"And I was fascinated,\nI wanted to know how do these guys do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435004,"text":"A few years back a group of researchers\nat University College London"},{"time":439059,"text":"brought a bunch of memory\nchampions into the lab."},{"time":441809,"text":"They wanted to know:"},{"time":443089,"text":"Do these guys have brains\nthat are somehow structurally,"},{"time":446048,"text":"anatomically different\nfrom the rest of ours?"},{"time":449246,"text":"The answer was no."},{"time":452561,"text":"Are they smarter than the rest of us?"},{"time":455307,"text":"They gave them a bunch of cognitive tests,\nand the answer was: not really."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459069,"text":"There was, however, one really\ninteresting and telling difference"},{"time":462315,"text":"between the brains of the memory champions"},{"time":464423,"text":"and the control subjects\nthat they were comparing them to."},{"time":467682,"text":"When they put these guys\nin an fMRI machine,"},{"time":470699,"text":"scanned their brains\nwhile they were memorizing numbers"},{"time":474060,"text":"and people's faces\nand pictures of snowflakes,"},{"time":476717,"text":"they found that the memory champions were\nlighting up different parts of the brain"},{"time":481597,"text":"than everyone else."},{"time":483288,"text":"Of note, they were using,\nor they seemed to be using,"},{"time":486573,"text":"a part of the brain that's involved\nin spatial memory and navigation."},{"time":491530,"text":"Why?"},{"time":492713,"text":"And is there something\nthat the rest of us can learn from this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":497847,"text":"The sport of competitive memorizing\nis driven by a kind of arms race where,"},{"time":504570,"text":"every year, somebody comes up with a new\nway to remember more stuff more quickly,"},{"time":509653,"text":"and then the rest of the field\nhas to play catch-up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512129,"text":"This is my friend Ben Pridmore,"},{"time":513772,"text":"three-time world memory champion."},{"time":515938,"text":"On his desk in front of him\nare 36 shuffled packs of playing cards"},{"time":521120,"text":"that he is about to try\nto memorize in one hour,"},{"time":524208,"text":"using a technique that he invented\nand he alone has mastered."},{"time":528287,"text":"He used a similar technique"},{"time":531032,"text":"to memorize the precise order\nof 4,140 random binary digits"},{"time":537854,"text":"in half an hour."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539929,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":541477,"text":"Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543573,"text":"And while there are a whole host of ways"},{"time":546423,"text":"of remembering stuff\nin these competitions,"},{"time":550458,"text":"everything, all of the techniques\nthat are being used,"},{"time":553140,"text":"ultimately come down to a concept"},{"time":555500,"text":"that psychologists refer to\nas \"elaborative encoding.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":559317,"text":"And it's well-illustrated\nby a nifty paradox"},{"time":561829,"text":"known as the Baker/baker paradox,\nwhich goes like this:"},{"time":565437,"text":"If I tell two people\nto remember the same word,"},{"time":568333,"text":"if I say to you,"},{"time":569900,"text":"\"Remember that\nthere is a guy named Baker.\""},{"time":573527,"text":"That's his name."},{"time":575033,"text":"And I say to you, \"Remember\nthat there is a guy who is a baker.\""},{"time":579821,"text":"Okay?"},{"time":581454,"text":"And I come back to you\nat some point later on,"},{"time":584660,"text":"and I say, \"Do you remember that word\nthat I told you a while back?"},{"time":588379,"text":"Do you remember what it was?\""},{"time":590275,"text":"The person who was told his name is Baker"},{"time":593542,"text":"is less likely to remember the same word"},{"time":596627,"text":"than the person was told\nhis job is a baker."},{"time":600238,"text":"Same word, different amount\nof remembering; that's weird."},{"time":603349,"text":"What's going on here?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":605016,"text":"Well, the name Baker\ndoesn't actually mean anything to you."},{"time":610034,"text":"It is entirely untethered\nfrom all of the other memories"},{"time":614271,"text":"floating around in your skull."},{"time":615786,"text":"But the common noun \"baker\" --\nwe know bakers."},{"time":619298,"text":"Bakers wear funny white hats."},{"time":621123,"text":"Bakers have flour on their hands."},{"time":622750,"text":"Bakers smell good\nwhen they come home from work."},{"time":625350,"text":"Maybe we even know a baker."},{"time":627089,"text":"And when we first hear that word,"},{"time":628842,"text":"we start putting these\nassociational hooks into it,"},{"time":631382,"text":"that make it easier to fish it\nback out at some later date."},{"time":635841,"text":"The entire art of what is going on\nin these memory contests,"},{"time":640352,"text":"and the entire art of remembering\nstuff better in everyday life,"},{"time":644188,"text":"is figuring out ways\nto transform capital B Bakers"},{"time":647973,"text":"into lower-case B bakers --"},{"time":649862,"text":"to take information\nthat is lacking in context,"},{"time":653174,"text":"in significance, in meaning,"},{"time":655254,"text":"and transform it in some way,"},{"time":656804,"text":"so that it becomes meaningful\nin the light of all the other things"},{"time":661026,"text":"that you have in your mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664620,"text":"One of the more elaborate\ntechniques for doing this"},{"time":667887,"text":"dates back 2,500 years to Ancient Greece."},{"time":671580,"text":"It came to be known as the memory palace."},{"time":673968,"text":"The story behind its creation\ngoes like this:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":677427,"text":"There was a poet called Simonides,\nwho was attending a banquet."},{"time":681858,"text":"He was actually the hired entertainment,"},{"time":683946,"text":"because back then, if you wanted\nto throw a really slamming party,"},{"time":687066,"text":"you didn't hire a D.J., you hired a poet."},{"time":690237,"text":"And he stands up, delivers his poem\nfrom memory, walks out the door,"},{"time":695696,"text":"and at the moment he does,"},{"time":697824,"text":"the banquet hall collapses."},{"time":700895,"text":"Kills everybody inside."},{"time":703753,"text":"It doesn't just kill everybody,"},{"time":705699,"text":"it mangles the bodies\nbeyond all recognition."},{"time":709793,"text":"Nobody can say who was inside,"},{"time":712166,"text":"nobody can say where they were sitting."},{"time":714754,"text":"The bodies can't be properly buried."},{"time":716993,"text":"It's one tragedy compounding another."},{"time":721613,"text":"Simonides, standing outside,"},{"time":723540,"text":"the sole survivor amid the wreckage,"},{"time":725671,"text":"closes his eyes and has this realization,"},{"time":730088,"text":"which is that in his mind's eye,"},{"time":732053,"text":"he can see where each of the guests\nat the banquet had been sitting."},{"time":737450,"text":"And he takes the relatives by the hand,"},{"time":739586,"text":"and guides them each\nto their loved ones amid the wreckage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":743998,"text":"What Simonides figured out at that moment,"},{"time":747020,"text":"is something that I think\nwe all kind of intuitively know,"},{"time":750243,"text":"which is that, as bad as we are\nat remembering names and phone numbers,"},{"time":755394,"text":"and word-for-word instructions\nfrom our colleagues,"},{"time":758417,"text":"we have really exceptional\nvisual and spatial memories."},{"time":763860,"text":"If I asked you to recount\nthe first 10 words of the story"},{"time":767607,"text":"that I just told you about Simonides,"},{"time":770233,"text":"chances are you would have\na tough time with it."},{"time":772827,"text":"But, I would wager\nthat if I asked you to recall"},{"time":777270,"text":"who is sitting on top\nof a talking tan horse"},{"time":781991,"text":"in your foyer right now,"},{"time":784031,"text":"you would be able to see that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":786498,"text":"The idea behind the memory palace"},{"time":788698,"text":"is to create this imagined edifice\nin your mind's eye,"},{"time":793285,"text":"and populate it with images\nof the things that you want to remember --"},{"time":797372,"text":"the crazier, weirder, more bizarre,"},{"time":800641,"text":"funnier, raunchier, stinkier the image is,"},{"time":804512,"text":"the more unforgettable it's likely to be."},{"time":807179,"text":"This is advice that goes\nback 2,000-plus years"},{"time":809949,"text":"to the earliest Latin memory treatises."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812506,"text":"So how does this work?"},{"time":814473,"text":"Let's say that you've been invited\nto TED center stage to give a speech,"},{"time":821280,"text":"and you want to do it from memory,"},{"time":823942,"text":"and you want to do it the way\nthat Cicero would have done it,"},{"time":828550,"text":"if he had been invited\nto TEDxRome 2,000 years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":832462,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":833684,"text":"What you might do"},{"time":835479,"text":"is picture yourself\nat the front door of your house."},{"time":841084,"text":"And you'd come up with some sort\nof crazy, ridiculous, unforgettable image,"},{"time":846333,"text":"to remind you that the first thing\nyou want to talk about"},{"time":849125,"text":"is this totally bizarre contest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":851407,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":852565,"text":"And then you'd go inside your house,"},{"time":854554,"text":"and you would see an image\nof Cookie Monster on top of Mister Ed."},{"time":859293,"text":"And that would remind you"},{"time":860562,"text":"that you would want to then\nintroduce your friend Ed Cook."},{"time":863933,"text":"And then you'd see\nan image of Britney Spears"},{"time":866400,"text":"to remind you of this funny\nanecdote you want to tell."},{"time":869212,"text":"And you'd go into your kitchen,"},{"time":870741,"text":"and the fourth topic\nyou were going to talk about"},{"time":873097,"text":"was this strange journey\nthat you went on for a year,"},{"time":875667,"text":"and you'd have some friends\nto help you remember that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881048,"text":"This is how Roman orators\nmemorized their speeches --"},{"time":884850,"text":"not word-for-word, which is just\ngoing to screw you up,"},{"time":888171,"text":"but topic-for-topic."},{"time":890877,"text":"In fact, the phrase \"topic sentence\" --"},{"time":894733,"text":"that comes from the Greek word \"topos,\""},{"time":897202,"text":"which means \"place.\""},{"time":898583,"text":"That's a vestige of when people used\nto think about oratory and rhetoric"},{"time":902794,"text":"in these sorts of spatial terms."},{"time":904708,"text":"The phrase \"in the first place,\""},{"time":907038,"text":"that's like \"in the first place\nof your memory palace.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":910611,"text":"I thought this was just fascinating,"},{"time":912357,"text":"and I got really into it."},{"time":913914,"text":"And I went to a few more\nof these memory contests,"},{"time":916696,"text":"and I had this notion\nthat I might write something longer"},{"time":919435,"text":"about this subculture\nof competitive memorizers."},{"time":922760,"text":"But there was a problem."},{"time":924577,"text":"The problem was that a memory contest"},{"time":927649,"text":"is a pathologically boring event."}]},{"cues":[{"time":930905,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":934088,"text":"Truly, it is like a bunch of people\nsitting around taking the SATs --"},{"time":938633,"text":"I mean, the most dramatic it gets"},{"time":940364,"text":"is when somebody\nstarts massaging their temples."},{"time":942697,"text":"And I'm a journalist,\nI need something to write about."},{"time":945268,"text":"I know that there's incredible stuff\nhappening in these people's minds,"},{"time":948720,"text":"but I don't have access to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":950489,"text":"And I realized, if I was going\nto tell this story,"},{"time":953664,"text":"I needed to walk\nin their shoes a little bit."},{"time":956482,"text":"And so I started trying\nto spend 15 or 20 minutes"},{"time":959597,"text":"every morning, before I sat\ndown with my New York Times,"},{"time":962359,"text":"just trying to remember something."},{"time":964929,"text":"Maybe it was a poem,"},{"time":966554,"text":"maybe it was names from an old yearbook\nthat I bought at a flea market."},{"time":971244,"text":"And I found that this was shockingly fun."},{"time":976739,"text":"I never would have expected that."},{"time":978652,"text":"It was fun because this is actually\nnot about training your memory."},{"time":981899,"text":"What you're doing, is you're trying\nto get better and better"},{"time":984919,"text":"at creating, at dreaming up,"},{"time":986975,"text":"these utterly ludicrous,\nraunchy, hilarious,"},{"time":990385,"text":"and hopefully unforgettable\nimages in your mind's eye."},{"time":993994,"text":"And I got pretty into it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":995577,"text":"This is me wearing my standard\ncompetitive memorizer's training kit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1001538,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1002775,"text":"It's a pair of earmuffs"},{"time":1004200,"text":"and a set of safety goggles\nthat have been masked over"},{"time":1008176,"text":"except for two small pinholes,"},{"time":1010282,"text":"because distraction is the competitive\nmemorizer's greatest enemy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1016684,"text":"I ended up coming back\nto that same contest"},{"time":1019673,"text":"that I had covered a year earlier,"},{"time":1021538,"text":"and I had this notion\nthat I might enter it,"},{"time":1023688,"text":"sort of as an experiment\nin participatory journalism."},{"time":1027537,"text":"It'd make, I thought, maybe\na nice epilogue to all my research."},{"time":1031105,"text":"Problem was, the experiment went haywire."},{"time":1035248,"text":"I won the contest --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1036447,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1037575,"text":"which really wasn't supposed to happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1040471,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1046731,"text":"Now, it is nice to be able\nto memorize speeches"},{"time":1051263,"text":"and phone numbers and shopping lists,"},{"time":1055386,"text":"but it's actually kind\nof beside the point."},{"time":1057902,"text":"These are just tricks."},{"time":1059746,"text":"They work because they're based\non some pretty basic principles"},{"time":1064516,"text":"about how our brains work."},{"time":1066803,"text":"And you don't have to be\nbuilding memory palaces"},{"time":1070244,"text":"or memorizing packs of playing cards"},{"time":1072506,"text":"to benefit from a little bit of insight\nabout how your mind works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1076907,"text":"We often talk about people\nwith great memories"},{"time":1079122,"text":"as though it were some sort\nof an innate gift,"},{"time":1081295,"text":"but that is not the case."},{"time":1083605,"text":"Great memories are learned."},{"time":1086835,"text":"At the most basic level,\nwe remember when we pay attention."},{"time":1090761,"text":"We remember when we are deeply engaged."},{"time":1093459,"text":"We remember when we are able to take\na piece of information and experience,"},{"time":1097625,"text":"and figure out why it is meaningful to us,"},{"time":1099731,"text":"why it is significant, why it's colorful,"},{"time":1102169,"text":"when we're able to transform it\nin some way that makes sense"},{"time":1106157,"text":"in the light of all of the other\nthings floating around in our minds,"},{"time":1109521,"text":"when we're able to transform\nBakers into bakers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1115116,"text":"The memory palace,\nthese memory techniques --"},{"time":1117283,"text":"they're just shortcuts."},{"time":1118719,"text":"In fact, they're not\neven really shortcuts."},{"time":1121684,"text":"They work because they make you work."},{"time":1125017,"text":"They force a kind of depth of processing,"},{"time":1128283,"text":"a kind of mindfulness,"},{"time":1129804,"text":"that most of us don't normally\nwalk around exercising."},{"time":1134494,"text":"But there actually are no shortcuts."},{"time":1137248,"text":"This is how stuff is made memorable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1140105,"text":"And I think if there's one thing\nthat I want to leave you with,"},{"time":1143755,"text":"it's what E.P., the amnesic who couldn't\neven remember he had a memory problem,"},{"time":1150307,"text":"left me with,"},{"time":1151528,"text":"which is the notion that our lives\nare the sum of our memories."},{"time":1158863,"text":"How much are we willing to lose"},{"time":1164853,"text":"from our already short lives,"},{"time":1168526,"text":"by losing ourselves\nin our Blackberries, our iPhones,"},{"time":1174122,"text":"by not paying attention\nto the human being across from us"},{"time":1179008,"text":"who is talking with us,"},{"time":1180583,"text":"by being so lazy that we're not\nwilling to process deeply?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1187463,"text":"I learned firsthand"},{"time":1189207,"text":"that there are incredible\nmemory capacities"},{"time":1192700,"text":"latent in all of us."},{"time":1195359,"text":"But if you want to live a memorable life,"},{"time":1198206,"text":"you have to be the kind of person"},{"time":1200539,"text":"who remembers to remember."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1202936,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1204112,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}